# Supabase Configuration
# Get these from your Supabase project settings
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Application URL
# For local development:
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# For production (set in Vercel dashboard):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://your-app-name.vercel.app

# Service Role Key (Optional - for server-side operations only)
# DO NOT expose this to the client or commit to version control
# Add this as a secret in Vercel if needed for privileged operations
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# Production Deployment Setup
# ============================
# 1. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in Vercel dashboard (Settings > Environment Variables)
# 2. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL to your production domain in Vercel dashboard
# 3. In Supabase dashboard:
#    - Go to Authentication > URL Configuration
#    - Set "Site URL" to your production domain
#    - Add your production domain to "Redirect URLs" (e.g., https://your-app.vercel.app/auth/callback)
# 4. Ensure RLS (Row Level Security) policies are configured on:
#    - profiles table: users can only access their own profile
#    - conversations table: users can only access their own conversations
#    - messages table: users can only access messages in their conversations
